      Prior to founding Legion Partners, Mr. White most recently served in various functions with Knight Vinke Asset Management, a European-based activist fund manager.  Positions included Managing Director and Chief Operating Officer, where he was responsible for finance, operations, legal, marketing and client service functions.  Mr. White also served as a director (Vice Chairman) of that firm.  He is a former Deputy Director of the Council of Institutional Investors (CII), where responsibilities included policy development and implementation.  Previous to Knight Vinke, Mr. White was a Portfolio Manager, Director of Corporate Governance, for the California Public Employees’ Retirement System (“CalPERS”), where he was responsible for all components of its Governance Program, including $3 billion in active management, policy development and implementation, proxy voting and focused engagement activities.  Prior to CalPERS, Mr. White was an Investment Officer – Deputy State Treasurer at the California State Treasurer’s Office, where his duties included fixed income portfolio analysis and trading, among other responsibilities.  Mr. White is a recognized expert in corporate governance within the institutional investment community.  He is Co-Chairman of the Executive Remuneration Committee of the International Corporate Governance Network (ICGN) and a former member of the Standing Advisory Group for the Public Company Accounting Oversight Board (PCAOB). Mr. White earned an MBA from California State University in Sacramento with a concentration in finance and is a CFA Charterholder.
    


    Prior to founding Legion Partners, Mr. Kiper most recently collaborated on several small-cap focused equity investments with Bradley Vizi.  Previously, Mr. Kiper worked for Shamrock Capital Advisors, the alternative investment vehicle of the Disney family where he served as Portfolio Manager of the Shamrock Activist Value Fund, a concentrated, long-only, activist fund with $800 million of assets under management.  While at Shamrock, Mr. Kiper led proxy contests that resulted in the election of multiple directors and the passing of a variety of governance related shareholder proposals.  Prior to Shamrock, Mr. Kiper founded and operated the Ridgestone Small Cap Value Fund, a small-cap targeted activist fund in association with Ridgestone Corporation.  Mr. Kiper began his career as an auditor with Ernst & Young, where he primarily focused on the financial services industry.  Mr. Kiper is a former director of Reddy Ice Holdings.  He graduated magna cum laude from the University of Nebraska with a Bachelor of Science in Business Administration degree in Accounting and is a Certified Public Accountant (inactive).
  


    Prior to founding Legion Partners, Mr. Vizi was an investment professional for Shamrock Capital Advisors, the alternative investment vehicle of the Disney Family, as part of the Shamrock Activist Value Fund.  Previous to Shamrock, Mr. Vizi was a member of the private equity group at Kayne Anderson Capital Advisors, a $25 billion investment firm focused on alternative investments.  Mr. Vizi currently serves on the Board of Directors for RCM Technologies, Inc. (NasdaqGM:RCMT) and is a member of the National Association of Corporate Directors.  He graduated from the Wharton School at the University of Pennsylvania with a Bachelor of Science degree and is a CFA Charterholder.
  


    Prior to joining Legion Partners as COO, Mr. Katz was co-founder and COO of Compass North Advisors and the sole founder and managing partner of K&P Capital, both long/short equity hedge funds.  Previous to founding K&P, Mr. Katz was CFO and VP Finance & Administration at WaterHealth International, a socially conscience, for-profit water purification company focused on developing countries.  Prior to WaterHealth, he was a senior analyst at Ivory Capital, a $2 billion long/short equity hedge fund.  Previous to Ivory, Mr. Katz was Vice President Mergers and Acquisitions in the Technology Group at Montgomery and Co.  Previously, he was a Senior Associate Consultant for Bain & Company before being appointed Director of Financial Planning and Analysis with Jostens Learning Corporation, a Bain Capital portfolio company focused on educational software development.  Mr. Katz graduated magna cum laude with a BA in economics and mathematics from Dartmouth College, with Phi Beta Kappa honors.  He later received an MBA from the Anderson School of Business as a Carter Fellow.  He serves as Treasurer on the Board of the Venice, California Boys and Girls Club.
  


